Like all the other species of this genus the young plants have enormously large leaves, such as are well described by Rum- phius in treating of the Songium. The only other genus, at least among the Dicotgsledones, that is equally remarkable in this respect, so far as I know, is the Artocarpas, in which the leaves of the young plants are not only of an enormous size, but of quite a different shape from those of the adult.
